Python Ping Plot and Graphing Tool

This is a Python-based tool that allows you to monitor the latency and packet loss of a network connection by sending ICMP Echo Request packets to a specified host or IP address and plotting the results in real-time. The tool can be useful for troubleshooting network issues and monitoring network performance.

Installation

The tool requires Python 3.x and the following packages to be installed:
curses
threading
socket
collections
argparse



Usage

To use the tool, simply run the ntwrkstatus3.py script with the desired arguments. The following arguments are available:


css
Copy code
python ping_plot.py -h example.com -t 2 -i 0.5 -c 100 -l 100

